  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nThe current implementation of binary to hexadecimal conversion in `Strings.sol` is straightforward but quite inefficient.  Its gas cost could be reduced several times.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nInstead of converting the nibbles one by one, it is possible to convert 32 nibbles at once.  See these links for examples of how this could be done:\r\n* https://stackoverflow.com/questions/67893318/solidity-how-to-represent-bytes32-as-string/69266989#69266989\r\n* https://gist.github.com/3sGgpQ8H/7c00e48af22b91effd5c37adc44908f3",
